Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Powassan (POW) Virus Market

Powassan (POW) virus market is expected to gain market growth in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Data Bridge Market Research analyses the market to account to grow at a CAGR of 4.50% in the above mentioned forecast period.

Powassan (POW) virus is a rare infection which is caused by the virus that is transmitted through the bite of the infected ticks. It is a member of the genus Flavivirus. This emerging arboviral infection can cause encephalitis, fever, headache, vomiting, seizures, meningitis and meningoencephalitis. Complications of powassan (POW) virus include recurrent headaches, muscle wasting and memory problems.

Rise in the prevalence of infection caused by the ticks, growing healthcare expenditure, increasing use of DEET-based insect repellents, rise in the investment by pharmaceutical companies to accelerate research activities, maintenance of good hygiene, rising initiatives by government and private organisations to spread awareness about the rare disease and its preventive measures are the factors that will expand the powassan (POW) virus market.

Rise in the research and development activities and growing focus of healthcare sector for new treatment therapies will provide beneficial opportunities for the powassan (POW) virus market in the forecast period of 2021-2028.

However, less awareness, lack of specific medication as the available treatment is supportive, high cost of diagnostic methods and treatment are the factors that will hinder the market growth and will further challenge the powassan (POW) virus market in the forecast period mentioned above.

